cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.SOC, cs.CL 

This paper deals with social recommendation and modeling user behavior on social networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also uses latent topic modeling, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also analyzes voting behavior, which falls under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Finally, the paper uses natural language processing techniques, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
